items.synopsis: After winning the toss and choosing to bowl, Australia bowls England out for 283 on day one at The Oval. Follow live.

title.children: Australia bowl England out after tea on day one at The Oval

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Anything below 300 is decent for Australia, but my word did they score them quickly and now put Australia into an awkward spot, batting in cloudy conditions with 90 minutes or so left in the day's play. The four-and-a-half dropped catches cost them dearly, to the tune of 111 runs, 80 of those from Harry Brook. But more than the runs, the drop of Brook shortly before lunch was a hammer blow momentum-wise. Now the Aussie top order has a huge job to do. If they're any more than one wicket down by stumps, that's a big win for England.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: England are all out for 283!

props.alt: Australia fielders bend over on the boundary as the ENglish crowd shout at them during an Ashes Test.

children.content: Anything below 300 is decent for Australia, but my word did they score them quickly and now put Australia into an awkward spot, batting in cloudy conditions with 90 minutes or so left in the day's play.

The four-and-a-half dropped catches cost them dearly, to the tune of 111 runs, 80 of those from Harry Brook. But more than the runs, the drop of Brook shortly before lunch was a hammer blow momentum-wise.
Now the Aussie top order has a huge job to do. If they're any more than one wicket down by stumps, that's a big win for England.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Another session that turned into a relatively even one - both teams had their moments in that, but England still edged their way to 250, while Australia took four wickets. The conditions seem pretty good for bowling out there - although it's hard to tell before both teams have a go. The lights are on, the clouds are rolling around above The Oval in South London and the ball is doing just a little bit through the air. The over rate is as bad as we've come to expect in the series - not helped by Todd Murphy being given just an odd over here and there. Will he be given more in the final session of the day? Jon Healy will be here to tell you all about it.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Tea: England 7-250 (Wood 23, Woakes 15)

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: England are falling apart here in the second session - another wicket falls to another loose shot as Brook drives at a wide one. Smith does well to take the catch and make it look easy.
